---

## ⚙️ Installation (Local Setup)

### 1. Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/your-username/auth-dashboard.git
cd auth-dashboard
```

---

### 2. Install dependencies

```
npm install
```

---

### 3. Create `.env` file

```
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

---

### 4. Run the server

```
node server.js
```

---

## 🔑 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint   | Description            |
| ------ | ---------- | ---------------------- |
| POST   | /signup    | Register new user      |
| POST   | /login     | Login user & get token |
| GET    | /users     | Get all users (auth)   |
| POST   | /users     | Add user               |
| PUT    | /users/:id | Update user            |
| DELETE | /users/:id | Delete user            |
| GET    | /profile   | Get user profile       |
| GET    | /admin     | Admin-only route       |
| POST   | /logout    | Logout user            |

---

## 🔐 Authentication Flow

1. User signs up → password is hashed
2. User logs in → JWT token generated
3. Token stored in browser (localStorage)
4. Token sent in headers for protected routes

```
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

---

## 🚀 Deployment Steps

### Backend (Render)

* Connect GitHub repo
* Add environment variables:

  * `MONGO_URI`
  * `JWT_SECRET`
* Deploy as Web Service

### Frontend (GitHub Pages)

* Push code to GitHub
* Enable GitHub Pages
* Update API URL to Render backend

---

## ⚠️ Common Issues

* ❌ MongoDB connection error → Check `MONGO_URI`
* ❌ 500 error → Check Render logs
* ❌ CORS error → Ensure `app.use(cors())`
* ❌ Token issues → Check `JWT_SECRET`

